=== Etymology ===
From Latin, ''abnōdō'' ("cut off knots"), from ''ab-'' ("from, away from") + ''nōdō'' ("knot, tie a knot").

=== Noun ===
'''abnodation''' (''plural'' abnodations)
# The act of cutting away the knots of trees.